ReviewContent: GOAT spot to jam, really fair prices.

Great rehearsal space! Rooms come with a PA system, variety of amps and drum kits. Lots of gear rentals are available too! Book an afternoon rehearsal, then stay for the evening activities like Sunday karaoke or every-other-Wednesday open mics! The venue is intimate, the people super friendly, and the staff passionate about what they do.
The best gear and best staff - they truly care and you can see the passion for music Thanks for doing this for the city

ReviewContent: nice practice space-turn that mutha up
Great place to rehearse in the city for hourly rates.
Best #shredspace ever!  This place is a diamond in the rough
A good first hostel experience.  Nice art and a surprising amount of privacy for a share living environment.  Very clean..
Rehearsin, Rockin and Rollin!
This place is great. Honestly, the quality of the instruments has gone way up over the last 2 years, and the drum sets, amps, etc. are really high quality.  The rates are reasonable, too.
Very nice rehearsal space. The rooms are clean and have everything you might possibly want. Staff are friendly and helpful. The central SF location is ideal.
Music CIty has rooms of all sizes & great atmosphere.  The staff is extremely helpful & nice.  Great place in a central SF location.  Highly recommended!   :) :) :)
Great place for practicing without noise complaints. Parking is a little tight. Its nice I dont have to lug my amp around!
Great place to rehearse.  Could use a bit more power on the bass amp in the small room tho.

Convenient online booking and decent price.  The rooms are a bit small and overheat easily and the sound bleeds more than in other studios.  The staff is really cool and helpful with any issues you may have with sound or equipment.  This place tends to be more crowded than other rehearsal studios Ive been to, so in order to get the full 3 hours you pay for, I recommend showing up early.
Professional yet Chill.  Always pleasant and accommodating.  Highly Recommended.
My neighbors are thankful I found this place. Now I go to Music City to smash on drums. Its nice. I like it.

I dig this place. The art on the walls is awesome. The rates are super reasonable and they provide all the heavy gear you dont want to have to lug around. They were even accommodating when I screwed up a booking time.
Affordable, but the gear is often broken or not working very well.  The service is not the best, either. You get what you pay for, I suppose.
Great place to jam out in the city. Love the pay-per-session model. Equipment is quality and makes for fun times
Hard to find the entrance, but it is a very neat idea and I believe it has lots of potential.

Great location off of Polk, solid rooms and equipment, amazing service. Always some cool local musicians playing shows on their stage, they do frequent open mics too. Good food and full bar is a plus, even can get stuff delivered to your rehearsal room

What a wonderful venue! The facilities are beautiful! We had the best time using a room for private karaoke for 10 people. We all loved the QR code for the karaoke app linked to the big screen and the QR code to order drinks and food delivered to the room. The karaoke app had so many songs and it was all easy to navigate and add songs to the queue. The food and drinks were good to boot! Highly recommend for a private karaoke party!

That is simply the most affectant rehearsal space ever, you can rent guitars bass and even a hotel room prayer to your rehearsal room reservation!!! It s unreal. I hiiighly recommend the experience with your band mates or along

ReviewContent: Amazing! Checked out their open mic and will definitely be coming back. Best part was the welcoming and inclusive vibes as soon as you walk in. Not only do they have a stage and full PA system, but a bar that also serves food! If you are a musician or love listening to live music, most definitely check this place out.

Musicians look no further!!! This place is amazing for rehearsals. Super affordable and brand new equipment. The drinks and food are also amazing. I love that they have live local music on most nights. What a way to bring together the community for music lovers. Shout out to Dolly, my favorite bartender Jaime, and front desk crew  Brian and Pia for always helping us out.

This is a wonderful venue! They serve the best tacos and they have the best hotel prices for single travelers. Truly a hidden gem located in the lower nob hill area. I really hope that more people check out this place a chance since it was magnificent.
Dolly and Jaime are great and the fried chicken sando was killer. Plus live music!
Love this new music venue. Also food is good too! I ordered beef tacos, French fries and virgin Bloody Mary. Delicious

I was so impressed with the overall vision of this place, I didnt take out my camera to show the wondrous space. Music City is the destination for music lovers, musicians, producers, and artists of any kind. If you celebrate any part of the San Francisco art scene, this place belongs on your list of places to be.
Awesome thanks
Best new venue for local and traveling artists. Dedicated to making SF a hotspot of musical talent again.

This is an okay experience as long as you have low standards and dont mind athletes foot. The shared showers are not clean, and gave my roommate the gnarliest case of athletes foot Ive ever witnessed first hand. She had to go to the ER. The hotel, overall, is pretty unclean. The private rooms are better than the shared rooms, but theyre still pretty dated and not really comfortable. They attempted to play up the aesthetic, without really understanding how to decorate or choose linens or anything. Its like a teenager with a very small budget was behind the entire construction and decoration of this place. Staff arent great, they have basic customer service skills but spend a lot of time hanging out with their friend/boyfriends when they should be focusing on answering phones or caring for customers or cleaning perhaps.
